WeRateDogs Twitter Insights & Analysis¶

Introduction¶

This project wrangles, analyzes, and visualizes the tweet archive of Twitter user @dog_rates, otherwise known as WeRateDogs. WeRateDogs is a Twitter account that rates people's dogs with a humorous comment about the dog. This analysis focuses on the distribution of ratings and the relationship between rating, retweets, and favorites.

Gathering Data¶

Data was obtained from three sources:

WeRateDogs twitter archive
Udacity's Twitter image prediction file
Twitter API

Assessing Data¶

Data was assessed visually and programmatically in python using a Jupyter notebook utilizing the following python libraries:

Pandas
Numpy
Tweepy
Requests
Json
Matplotlib
Seaborn
Io
Urllib
PIL

This analysis focuses on only original tweets with images that were retweeted on or before August 1 2017. Any data failing to meet this criteria is not included in this analysis.

Cleaning Data¶

Before cleaning the data, all data was copied to new dataframes. Quality and tidiness issues were documented utilizing the Define-Code-Test framework. Once cleaned, all data was merged into a master dataframe and saved to csv.

Storing Data¶

The gathered, cleaned, and assessed master dataframe was saved to the twitter_archive_master.csv file.

Analysis & Visualization¶
